amine the (Self-)Reflective Effects of History Teaching -- tContributors0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aThis book presents new developments in Scandinavian memory cultures related to World War II and the Holocaust by combining this focus with the perspective of history didactics. The theoretical framework of historical consciousness offers an approach linking individual and collective uses and re-uses of the past to the question how history can and should be taught. It also offers some examples of good practice in this field.The book promotes a teaching practice which, in taking the social constructivist notions of historical consciousness as a starting point, can contribute to self-reflecting and critical thinking - being fundamental for any democratic political culture.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2018: Backlist Collection  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zScandinaviaxPsychological aspects. 0aNational socialism and historiographyzScandinavia. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zScandinaviaxHistoriography. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zScandinaviaxPsychological aspects. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zScandinaviaxStudy and teeaching. 4aCultural Studies. 4aEducation. 4aHistorical Consciousness. 4aHistory Didactics. 4aHistory of the 20th Century. 4aHistory. 4aWorld War II. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aEducation.  aHistorical Consciousness.  aHistory Didactics.  aHistory of the 20th Century.  aHistory.  aWorld War II.1 aAhonen, Sirkka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.g